Wait, actually let me re-read the function carefully:

```rust
pub fn safe_truncate(s: &str, max_bytes: usize) -> &str {
    if s.len() <= max_bytes {
        return s;
    }
    let mut b = max_bytes;
    while b > 0 && !s.is_char_boundary(b) {
        b -= 1;
    }
    &s[..b]
}
```

If `max_bytes` is 0 and `s.len() > 0`, then `b = 0`, the `while` loop doesn't execute (since `b > 0` is false), and we return `&s[..0]` which is an empty string. 0 is always a char boundary. So that's fine.

