OK, this seems well-done. Let me look at areas where I can make a meaningful improvement. Let me look at the `context.rs` `truncate` function more carefully. It's inefficient compared to format/mod.rs's `truncate_with_ellipsis`:

```rust
// context.rs
fn truncate(text: &str, max_chars: usize) -> String {
    if text.chars().count() <= max_chars {
        return text.to_string();
    }
    let mut out = text.chars().take(max_chars).collect::<String>();
    out.push_str("...");
    out
}

// format/mod.rs
pub fn truncate_with_ellipsis(s: &str, max: usize) -> String {
    match s.char_indices().nth(max) {
        Some((idx, _)) => format!("{}…", &s[..idx]),
        None => s.to_string(),
    }
}
```

The `format/mod.rs` version is more efficient because `char_indices().nth(max)` is O(max), while `text.chars().count()` is O(n) for the entire string. But both are private/used in different ways.

